# Roles, auth, and login

Student views are for students only. Admin/teacher views are for those
roles only. Demo mode must never log in as superadmin — `demoLogin()` in
`src/utils/storage.ts` always returns the student demo account, and that
hard rule must not regress.

Before changing anything in the auth flow, verify end-to-end:
- Manual email/password login.
- Google login (uses normalized email — see `normalizeEmail()` in
  `src/utils/storage.ts`).
- Logout button ("Cerrar sesión") clears the session.
- Role-based redirect after login lands on the right surface.
- `localStorage` (`edutic_*` keys) and `sessionStorage` behavior are
  preserved.
- Sede admins created with a temp password are forced to
  `/cambiar-contrasena`; Google sign-in bypasses that flow.

Never let a lower role reach a higher-role screen. Never store or display
the user's current password — only a freshly generated temp value, once.
